The paper deals with the synthesis of implementations of epistemic protocol specifications, which involves reasoning about knowledge and actions of multiple agents. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes an approach to model checking problems, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Distributed Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the complexity of constructing approximations, which is relevant to Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Programming Languages (cs.PL).
